1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,172
When you start the activities, they will follow the same order as this lesson.

2
00:00:05,122 --> 00:00:09,918
First, you do a warm-up: Show a plain sentence and a title.

3
00:00:09,918 --> 00:00:12,934
Ask which one is easier to spot and why.

4
00:00:12,934 --> 00:00:17,500
Then you answer quick checks, so we know the key words make sense.

5
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:26,467
Next, you practise the real computer skill: Type a useful title, select it, make it bigger, make it bold and centre it.

6
00:00:26,467 --> 00:00:32,649
You may also type a short answer, for example: Type a title for a simple document.

7
00:00:32,649 --> 00:00:39,429
At the end, you finish with a stretch or reflection: Use alignment buttons to show how text moves.

8
00:00:39,429 --> 00:00:42,228
Return the final title to centre.

9
00:00:42,228 --> 00:00:44,779
Take one activity at a time.

10
00:00:44,779 --> 00:00:49,334
If you need help, ask staff, then try the next step yourself.

